name: Jette Feigenbaum
body:
## Personal

* Born on January 28, 1991
* Can speak Estonian, English, French
* I like dogs, tumblr, blogging and coding
* [Personal website](http://jette-feigenbaum.com)
* [My Android apps](https://play.google.com/store/apps/developer?id=Jette)

## Know about
### JavaScript, Ruby on Rails, CSS, HTML, jQuery, Mobile Applications, WordPress, Backbone.js, Mockups, Photoshop

## Have worked as
### Project manager in Desk Rock

Feb 2013 - Sept 2013

Learned Ruby on Rails, Git, Backbone, got to know more about databases and a got great overview of how agile IT companies' workflow looks like. Was mostly project leading and facilitating/organizing things for the developers team, but got to code a bit myself, too.

### IT consultant in Koertekeskus

Jan 2012 - May 2012

As it was a small company, I really did everything from managing the company's website and Facebook profile to writing newsletters and consulting the clients.

## Have studied

### IT systems development in The Estonian Information Technology College

2012-2013

Through IT-college I was introduced to the world of IT and I was shown what can be done with the help of techology, what are the current issues and challenges, 

Courses like Intro to Java, Web applications

### Ecology in Tartu University

2010-2011

I got a deeper look into how the world works, what kind of living beings are around us, what do they have in common to humans and what things are different. My respect for all living beings on Earth doubled.

Courses like Behavior ecology, Zoo-semiotics, Organic chemistry, Genetics, Cell biology, Geology, Evolution, Intro to Zoology

### Hugo Treffneri GÃ¼mnaasium

2007-2010

The best thing about this school was the people. I met very motivated and bright people there, who all had a different outlook to the world and deeper knowledge in some field nobody else knew about.
